<p><strong>string</strong> is a keyword, and you can't use string as an identifier. </p>

<p><strong>String</strong> is not a keyword, and you can use it as an identifier:</p>

<p><strong>Example</strong></p>

<pre><code>string String = "I am a string";
</code></pre>

<p>The keyword <code>string</code>  is an alias for
 <code>System.String</code> aside from the keyword issue, the two are exactly
 equivalent.</p>

<pre><code> typeof(string) == typeof(String) == typeof(System.String)
</code></pre>
